div1.p:
J. Wood. I was very ill, and my husband was out of town; I lay down on the bed, not having much sleep for several nights;
Ann Bassey
came in. I desired her to sit down, and if any body came in for her to awake me; I thought I could have trusted her, and while I was fast asleep, my hand, with my wedding ring on my finger, being on the outside the bed, she took my ring off, it was rather too big for my finger, and she took the other things mentioned, and went away; when I awaked I miss 'd her and them.
